        <h1>LeetCode 1288: Remove Covered Intervals (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given an array of intervals where intervals[i] = [li, ri], remove all intervals that are covered by
                another interval in the list. An interval [a, b] is covered by interval [c, d] if c &lt;= a and b &lt;=
                d. Return the number of remaining intervals.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: intervals = [[1,4],[3,6],[2,8]]<br>
                Output: 2<br>
                Explanation: Interval [3,6] is covered by [2,8] since 2 &lt;= 3 and 6 &lt;= 8. After removing [3,6],
                there are 2 intervals remaining.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int removeCoveredIntervals(vector&lt;vector&lt;int&gt;&gt;&amp; intervals) {
        int total = intervals.size();
        int coveredCount = 0;
        for (int curr = 0; curr &lt; total; curr++) {
            for (int other = 0; other &lt; total; other++) {
                if (curr == other)
                    continue;
                // Check if the current interval is covered by another one.
                if (intervals[other][0] &lt;= intervals[curr][0] &amp;&amp;
                    intervals[curr][1] &lt;= intervals[other][1]) {
                    coveredCount++;
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
        return total - coveredCount;
    }
};</code></pre>
